Sirsi-API version 0.01
======================

Sirsi::API is a pure-Perl module that allows executing Sirsi API commands
via apiserver and parsing the responses.

INSTALLATION

To install this module type the following:

   perl Makefile.PL
   make
   make test
   make install

DEPENDENCIES

Perl >= 5.10

This module requires these other modules and libraries:

Parse::RecDescent
JSON

SUGGESTED

MARC::Charset 
	Allows for conversion of MARC8 encoded output from Sirsi to
	UTF-8


Note the source distribution, but not any installable package created
from it using the usual "perl Makefile.PL; make dist" routine, contains
a sample-cgi.pl script intended to serve as a basic usage example.

